# Testes de Estado Flutter

## Testando ChangeNotifier

```dart
import 'package:flutter_test/flutter_test.dart';
import 'package:my_app/notifiers/counter_notifier.dart';

void main() {
  late CounterNotifier notifier;

  setUp(() {
    notifier = CounterNotifier();
  });

  test('valor inicial e zero', () {
    expect(notifier.count, 0);
  });

  test('increment aumenta o contador', () {
    notifier.increment();
    expect(notifier.count, 1);
  });

  test('decrement nao vai abaixo de zero', () {
    notifier.decrement();
    expect(notifier.count, 0);
  });

  test('notifica listeners ao mudar', () {
    var notified = false;
    notifier.addListener(() => notified = true);
    notifier.increment();
    expect(notified, isTrue);
  });
}
```

## Testando BLoC

```dart
import 'package:bloc_test/bloc_test.dart';
import 'package:my_app/blocs/counter_bloc.dart';

void main() {
  blocTest<CounterBloc, int>(
    'emite [1] quando Increment e adicionado',
    build: () => CounterBloc(),
    act: (bloc) => bloc.add(Increment()),
    expect: () => [1],
  );

  blocTest<CounterBloc, int>(
    'emite [1, 2, 1] para sequencia de eventos',
    build: () => CounterBloc(),
    act: (bloc) {
      bloc.add(Increment());
      bloc.add(Increment());
      bloc.add(Decrement());
    },
    expect: () => [1, 2, 1],
  );
}
```

## Testando Riverpod

```dart
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'package:flutter_test/flutter_test.dart';
import 'package:my_app/providers/counter_provider.dart';

void main() {
  test('counterProvider inicia em zero', () {
    final container = ProviderContainer();
    addTearDown(container.dispose);

    expect(container.read(counterProvider), 0);
  });

  test('counterProvider incrementa', () {
    final container = ProviderContainer();
    addTearDown(container.dispose);

    container.read(counterProvider.notifier).increment();
    expect(container.read(counterProvider), 1);
  });

  test('provider com override de dependencia', () {
    final container = ProviderContainer(
      overrides: [
        userRepositoryProvider.overrideWithValue(MockUserRepository()),
      ],
    );
    addTearDown(container.dispose);
  });
}
```

## Mock de Notifiers

```dart
class MockCounterNotifier extends Mock implements CounterNotifier {}

// Em widget tests com Provider
testWidgets('exibe contador', (tester) async {
  final mockNotifier = MockCounterNotifier();
  when(() => mockNotifier.count).thenReturn(42);

  await tester.pumpWidget(
    ChangeNotifierProvider<CounterNotifier>.value(
      value: mockNotifier,
      child: const MaterialApp(home: CounterScreen()),
    ),
  );
  expect(find.text('42'), findsOneWidget);
});
```

## Convencoes

- `setUp` para criar instancia nova a cada teste
- `blocTest` para testar BLoCs (nao testar manualmente)
- `ProviderContainer` para testes unitarios de providers
- `addTearDown(container.dispose)` para limpeza
- Overrides para injetar mocks em testes de integracao
